               <head>Grant; Rickinghall Superior, etc.; c. 1260-90</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Rikighal</surname></persName></persName>, grants to 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, the abbot of <orgName role="abbot" key="org_104015">St. Edmund</orgName></persName>,
                  one wind-mill in the village of <placeName key="place_105468">Rickinghall Superior (Upper Rikinghale)</placeName>, with the site and land 
                  adjacent. For this charter of donation the said abbot gave to the said Hugh 20 marks and 2
                  pieces of land reckoned as 3 acres at <placeName key="place_105462">Redgrave</placeName>. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1260" notAfter="1290" precision="low">c. 1260-90</origDate>.) 
